column12: Also known as Dimidium. First exoplanet discovered orbiting a main-sequence star
Least massive exoplanet known. Also known as Draugr.
The first exoplanet discovered around a brown dwarf
First extrasolar planet discovered by indirect imaging (visible light)[3]
The most likely known candidate for being an ocean planet.[4] Nicknamed "water world".
Has the most eccentric orbit of any known exoplanet[5]
The faintest ground-based detection of a transiting planet[6]
Has the largest orbit for a circumbinary planet
Shortest orbital period of any known exoplanet
Largest separation from its host star, for any exoplanet
Has a reddish color, and may be a brown dwarf
Nearest exoplanet to the Solar System, and is potentially habitable
Extremely eccentric orbit around an evolved red giant
Largest exoplanet in relation to its star
First exoplanet discovered by scientists based in India.
First transiting exoplanet found by an amateur astronomer
